I'm a bit surprised by so many people giving Gura a pat on the back for going against expectations with her song, when I thought she very much went with my expectations. I thought that Gura's art ideas were really cool, but I can see why they went with art number 1. Number 2 was cool but it made the darkness seem external when the image was supposed to portray a battle against the "Self". I think Number 3 was my personal favorite idea but it's a bit complex and might not get the idea across quickly, which is what you would want for a song cover. Gura is really creative.
